  "prompt": "Can you confirm if money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (often referred to as \"dirty money\") appear legitimate by passing it through a series of transactions or financial systems. This practice is a criminal offense because it facilitates and conceals criminal activities such as drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, and terrorism financing.\n\nMost countries have strict anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations in place to detect, prevent, and prosecute such activities. International bodies like the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)** also work to set global standards and promote effective enforcement of anti-money laundering measures. Penalties for money laundering can include hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
